'''''Young Jedi Knights: Crisis at Crystal Reef''''' is a [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] young-adult novel written by [[Kevin J. Anderson]] and [[Rebecca Moesta]]. It is the fourteenth and final book in the ''[[Star Wars: Young Jedi Knights]]'' series, and it was first published by [[Berkley Boulevard]] in [[August]] [[1998]]. It also includes a sixteen-page preview of [[Lucasfilm]]'s ''Alien Chronicles: The Crimson Claw''. The novel was reprinted in ''[[Young Jedi Knights: Under Black Sun]]'' ([[1999]]).

==Publisher's summary==
''Anja Gallandro planned to destroy the Solo family. But now she fights an intense inner battle—against her growing spice addiction, and her growing friendship with Jacen and Jaina. She no longer knows where her loyalties lie. In desperation for spice, she steals a ship and flees the Jedi academy.''

''The young Jedi Knights give chase, following her from the spice mines of Kessel to the dangerous paradise of Crystal Reef. But Anja has been a pawn all along in a game that is much bigger than all of them. And they just landed in the middle of it&hellip;''

==Plot summary==
Racked by [[Andris/Legends|spice]] withdraw, [[Anja Gallandro|Anja]] steals [[Lightning Rod|Zekk's ship]]. Upon discovering that [[Czethros]] was behind the long, terrible war on [[Anobis]], she vows to strike back against her former master. Anja voyages to [[Dac|Mon Calamari]] to scuttle Czethros' [[Spice/Legends|spice]]-[[Smuggler/Legends|smuggling]] operation there. [[Darth Caedus|Jacen]] and his friends, concerned over Anja's behavior, find her on Mon Calamari with the help of [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] and [[Mon Calamari/Legends|Mon Calamari]] [[Ambassador/Legends|ambassador]] [[Cilghal]]. Cilghal uses her [[Force healing/Legends|Force healing]] abilities to clear Anja of her addiction. Meanwhile, [[Jaina Solo Fel|Jaina]] and [[Lowbacca|Lowbacca]] corner Czethros in the [[Spice mines of Kessel/Legends|spice mines of Kessel]]. Rather than be captured, Czethros throws himself into a vat of [[Carbonite/Legends|carbonite]], where he is flash-frozen. Returning to [[Yavin 4/Legends|Yavin 4]], the young [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] are honored in a graduation ceremony that seems them promoted to the rank of Jedi Knights.

==Continuity==
Because details of the [[Padawan/Legends|padawan]] – [[Jedi Master/Legends|Master]] apprenticeship were not known to ''[[Star Wars]]'' book authors at this time, the graduation of the students to [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knights]] does not signify the end of their training. Although the students are described as "fully trained Jedi Knights" at this point in the timeline, [[Darth Caedus|Jacen]], [[Jaina Solo Fel|Jaina]], and [[Anakin Solo|Anakin]] begin the [[Star Wars: The New Jedi Order|''New Jedi Order'']] series apprenticed to other Masters.<ref name="TERC" />

